    "terms.body":                 "<h2>1. The toolkit (the code)</h2><p>The ForgeLM Python package and its source code are released under the <strong>Apache License 2.0</strong>. You can use it, modify it, embed it in commercial products, and redistribute it under the terms of that licence. The full text is at <a href=\"https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0</a>.</p><p>The toolkit is provided <strong>\"as is\", without warranty of any kind</strong> — see the <em>Disclaimer of Warranty</em> and <em>Limitation of Liability</em> sections of the licence. Fine-tuning models is a real-world activity with real-world consequences (safety, accuracy, regulatory exposure); you remain responsible for the systems you build with it.</p><h2>2. The website (this domain)</h2><p>The website's HTML, CSS, JavaScript, copy, and graphics are also covered by Apache 2.0 unless otherwise marked. You may fork the site, but the trademark — the name <strong>\"ForgeLM\"</strong> and the logo — is reserved (see §3).</p><p>You may not use the site to:</p><ul><li>impersonate the project or its maintainers;</li><li>scrape it for the purpose of training a model that would compete with the toolkit's positioning without crediting it;</li><li>send spam through the contact form, attempt to reverse-engineer Formspree's anti-abuse measures, or submit malicious payloads.</li></ul><h2>3. Trademark</h2><p>\"ForgeLM\" and the forge mark are trademarks of the project. You may use the name to truthfully refer to the toolkit (e.g., \"we fine-tuned with ForgeLM\") and to link to this site. You may not use the name or mark in a way that suggests endorsement, official partnership, or origination by us when none exists.</p><h2>4. Third-party software</h2><p>ForgeLM depends on third-party libraries (HuggingFace Transformers, TRL, PEFT, bitsandbytes, Unsloth, datasketch, pypdf, etc.) — each governed by its own licence. Compatibility is documented in <code>pyproject.toml</code>.</p><h2>5. Models and datasets</h2><p>ForgeLM is a tool that operates on models and datasets you supply. Their licences (Llama 3 community licence, Mistral commercial terms, dataset CC-BY-NC-SA, etc.) <strong>govern your use of those artefacts</strong>, not Apache 2.0. ForgeLM does not grant you any rights in the underlying weights or training data.</p><h2>6. No professional advice</h2><p>Statements on this site about EU AI Act compliance, GDPR, ISO 27001, or any other regulatory regime are <strong>technical descriptions</strong>, not legal advice. The toolkit produces evidence; certification, conformity assessment, and DPIA reviews remain a sociotechnical process you must conduct with qualified counsel and (where applicable) a notified body.</p><h2>7. Liability</h2><p>To the maximum extent permitted by law, the project, its maintainers, and contributors are not liable for any indirect, incidental, special, consequential, or punitive damages, or for any loss of profits, revenues, data, or goodwill arising out of your use of the toolkit or the website. The Apache 2.0 limitation of liability applies in full.</p><h2>8. Changes</h2><p>If we update these terms, the date at the top changes. Material changes are noted in the project's <code>CHANGELOG.md</code>. Continued use of the site after a change constitutes acceptance of the updated terms.</p><h2>9. Governing law</h2><p>The toolkit's licence is the sole governing instrument for the code. For disputes specifically about the website's content (e.g., trademark misuse), Turkish law applies, and the courts of Istanbul are competent — without prejudice to your mandatory consumer protections in your jurisdiction of residence.</p><h2>10. Contact</h2><p>Questions or notices: open the <a href=\"contact.html\">contact form</a>.</p>"
